label: imaging data set
definition: A data set that is comprised of structured measurements about some entity and its associated metadata using pixels (2D), voxels (3D), or an arbitrary number of dimensions. An image data set can be the source from which an image is produced.
example of usage: The output produced by a digital imaging technique, such as microscopy, MRI, or CT.

label: magnetic resonance imaging data set
definition: An imaging data set whose information content originates from some MR imaging assay and is about some MRI participant.
example of usage: The DICOM file produced by an MRI machine when a multiple sclerosis patient undergoes a brain scan.

label: raw imaging data set
definition: An imaging data set that encodes measurement values produced by some instrument before undergoing a data transformation.
example of usage: The untransformed (""k-space"") data produced by an MRI machine, prior to mathematical transformation into a form that corresponds to the anatomical structure of the brain.
